latestPosts.caption:
Oops story time: I don’t train in running, I just do it where I have a clean beach in front of me… after Covid my lungs and body took a hit and it’s been building its way back strength and stamina wise. I haven’t felt 100% like myself since and am not sure I ever will. But that’s when mind over matter comes in and also @milindrunning, who I can’t say no to, coz he inspires endlessly! So he asked me to be the mascot of the 10km run and the last time I did that for him was over ten years ago and also the first and last time I had run 10km!
 It’s true when they say what doesn’t kill you makes you stronger, footsteps even lighter and I am definitely not lonely when I run ALONE. 
And seeing all those incredible women out there in all categories doing their thing was amazing, the energy infectious! And my sweet @ankita_earthy leading the way with her complete transformation and inspiring so many! 
I ran all the way, didn’t stop, no training ever, didn’t need my asthma pump and paced myself till the end. The first 3 kms my body was ready to quit but then it went into auto pilot! Loved how I felt before the run, during and after! The only kind of running you do that isn’t away from things but towards self love is this! 🏃‍♀️💖 
And to my beautiful girls who showed up, finished with a smile and did themselves and me so proud! Thankyou 🩷

And to @adidasindia thankyou for dressing me and always making me feel that extra bit comfy & athletic! 💙

Lastly to @pinkathonindia thank you for the positive encouraging energy 🩷
